cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image processing and specifically focuses on multimodal images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a framework based on dictionary learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information theory (cs.IT) as it tries to capture similarities and disparities between different image modalities. Additionally, the paper uses sparse transforms, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with multimodal data, which is a topic of interest in multimedia (cs.MM).
